From f8a765d85daf5d9e84861fb339267487703c813b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Pedro Maione <pedro.maione@9elements.com>
Date: Tue, 3 Mar 2026 13:38:22 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] misc: amd-sbi: add SB-RMI revision 0x21 (Turin) protocol
 support

Turin processors implement APML SB-RMI rev 0x21, which uses a 16-bit
I2C register address space and a u16 thread field in the CPUID/MCA MSR
protocol, replacing the 8-bit address and the THREAD128CS workaround
used in rev 0x20.

Add configure_regmap to auto-detect the correct register
address width at probe time.  The 16-bit path is attempted first since
issuing a 1-byte address transaction on a Turin device can cause an
unrecoverable error requiring a system reboot.  If the revision read
does not return 0x21, the driver falls back to an 8-bit regmap.  Up to
MAX_RETRY (5) attempts are made to tolerate slow firmware init.

Return -EPROBE_DEFER from sbrmi_get_max_pwr_limit() when firmware
signals not-ready (fw_ret_code == 0x01).  Defer the power_cap_max cache
population to the first hwmon read to tolerate late firmware readiness.

Tested on DL365:

```
root@hpe-proliant-g11:~# dmesg | grep -i sbr
[    2.851824] sbrmi-i2c 42-0038: sbrmi-supply not enabled, deferring probe
[    2.872904] sbrmi-i2c 43-003c: sbrmi-supply not enabled, deferring probe
root@hpe-proliant-g11:~# cat /sys/bus/i2c/devices/43-003c/hwmon/hwmon5/power1_input
53625000
root@hpe-proliant-g11:~# cat /sys/bus/i2c/devices/43-003c/hwmon/hwmon5/power1_cap
155000000
root@hpe-proliant-g11:~# cat /sys/bus/i2c/devices/43-003c/hwmon/hwmon5/power1_cap_max
155000000
root@hpe-proliant-g11:~# ls /dev/sbrmi-*
/dev/sbrmi-3c
```

Signed-off-by: Pedro Maione <pedro.maione@9elements.com>
